Description: This is a coloring of rach residue according to its shell in our onion model.
This is a coloring of each residue according to its Shannon Entropy in our alignment. Blue is most conserved and red is least conserved.
This is a coloring of each residue according to its index in our secondary structure. The 5S is placed at the end. There is a rainbow gradient ranging from blue on the 5' end to red on the 3' end.
This is a coloring of each residue according to its placement in a traditional secondary structure domain.
This is a coloring of all residues which contact the selected proteins. Each color represents a different protein in your list of selected proteins
This is a set of base-base interactions as defined in FR3D.
This is a set of base-phosphate interactions as defined in FR3D.
This is a set of base-sugar interactions as defined in FR3D.
This is a set of base-base stacking as defined in FR3D.
